PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1777497070
OL,3,CEurope warming at twice as fast as the
OL,4,Cglobal average, climate report shows
OL,6,FPut together by Copernicus, the
OL,7,FEuropean Earth Observation programme
OL,8,Fand the World Meteorological
OL,9,FOrganisation, the report comes after a
OL,10,Fyear of extreme weather in the UK,
OL,11,Fincluding the hottest summer on record
OL,12,Fand widespread droughts.
OL,14,FIn the wider continent, the heat has
OL,15,Fhad a number of impacts.
OL,17,FGlaciers in all European regions saw a
OL,18,Fnet mass loss, with Iceland recording
OL,19,Fits second-largest glacier loss on
OL,20,Frecord.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1777497070
OL,3,CEurope warming at twice as fast as the
OL,4,Cglobal average, climate report shows
OL,6,FThe consequences of melting glaciers
OL,7,Fwere most obvious in the Swiss village
OL,8,Fof Blatten: 130 houses and a church
OL,9,Fwere crushed when 20 million tonnes of
OL,10,Fice from the Birch Glacier fell down
OL,11,Fthe mountain onto the town.
OL,13,FAlthough residents had been evacuated,
OL,14,Fone man died.
OL,16,FThe report also showed that Europe
OL,17,Falso had its worst year ever for
OL,18,Fwildfires.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
