OL,3,CEurope warming at twice as fast as the
OL,4,Cglobal average, climate report shows
OL,6,FA record one million hectares of land
OL,7,Fwas burnt, including from fires across
OL,8,FSpain and Portugal that burnt across
OL,9,Fthe Iberian peninsula in August.
OL,11,FFive of Europe's warmest years on
OL,12,Frecord have occurred since 2019 and
OL,13,FCopernicus scientists say there are
OL,14,Fseveral reasons that Europe is heating
OL,15,Fup so quickly.
OL,17,FOne of the reasons for the rising
OL,18,Ftemperatures is our proximity to the
OL,19,FArctic which is heating up three times
OL,20,Ffaster than the global average.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
