OL,3,CEurope warming at twice as fast as the
OL,4,Cglobal average, climate report shows
OL,6,F"Just as we're losing sea ice and
OL,7,Fglacier ice and cloud cover, Europe is
OL,8,Fbecoming sunnier," explained Dr
OL,9,FSamantha Burgess, Deputy Director at
OL,10,FCopernicus Climate Change Service.
OL,12,F"This means we're getting more of the
OL,13,Fsun's energy hitting the surface of
OL,14,FEurope than they reflected off snow or
OL,15,Fice or clouds."
OL,17,FThe reduction of pollution also has an
OL,18,Funexpected effect.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1777497070
OL,3,CEurope warming at twice as fast as the
OL,4,Cglobal average, climate report shows
OL,6,F"There's been huge improvements in air
OL,7,Fquality over the last three decades,"
OL,8,FDr Burgess said.
OL,10,F"So while these improvements in air
OL,11,Fquality really save a lot of lives, it
OL,12,Falso means without that pollution in
OL,13,Fthe atmosphere, we are seeing less low
OL,14,Flevel cloud, which means we're getting
OL,15,Fmore solar radiation hitting the
OL,16,Fsurface here."
OL,18,FHowever, there was on piece of good
OL,19,Fnews to be found in the report.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
